<br>
AMD-specific:  <a href=http://www.amdmb.com>AMDMb.com</a> (news site), <a href=http://www.athlonoc.com>Athlon Overclockers'</a>.<br>
<br>
Nvidia-specific:  <a href=http://www.nvnews.net>NVnews</a> (news site), <a href=http://www.the-ctrl-alt-del.com>The Ctrl-Alt-Del.com</a> (good news site with a full set of leaked drivers).<br>
<br>
Win2K-specific:  <a href=http://www.ntcompatible>NT Compatible</a> (excellent), <a href=http://w2kgamer.com>Win2K Gamer</a> -- these will occasionally review hardware as well.<br>
<br>
More hardcore/technical sites (be careful with newbie questions on the forums - do a search;):  <a href=http://www.hardocp.com>HardOCP</a> (excellent forums - also check the <a href=http://www.hardocp.com/links.html>links</a> for other good sites), <a href=http://www.iamnotageek.com>Iamnotageek.com</a>, <a href=http://www.voidyourwarranty.net>Void Your Warranty</a>.<br>
<br>
There are many I left out, but if you check out the link lists on these sites and find the common denominators, you'll be in good shape.  ;)  Also, the sites I list as "news" sites, while not doing many of their own reviews, will mostly link you to other sites reviewing stuff.  They are an <i>invaluable</i> resource because they read tons of sites and link you to the good articles -- one search of their news can go a long way.  Finally, a google search on your products plus some good keywords is usually a good idea.<br>
<br>
In case you don't want to spend hours combing through sites, my suggestion is as follows:  Athlon 1.2 is a good price point now; you can't really go wrong with Asus motherboards, except I'd avoid the A7<b><u>A</b></u>266 due to its crappy chipset; the Asus GeForce2 is a good but overpriced card -- save yourself some money; with DDR memory at around $45 for 256Mb of PC2100 CAS2.5, I'd get 512 for sure, especially if you are going the Win2K/WinXP route. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utudamorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tudamorf</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://lag999.homestead.com/files/biggrin.gif width=15 height=15 BORDER=0> at: 7/24/01 4:22:21 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubrairwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brairwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/23/01 9:02:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneralot.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1128.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Good Hardware Info site</span><hr size=1> Wait a few months to upgrade. With Toms Hardware and what Tudamorf posted, you have a good place to start.<br>
